# 🤖 AI Telegram ChatBot (Groq + LLaMA 3.1 + Python)

An AI-powered Telegram chatbot built using Python, python-telegram-bot, and Groq API (LLaMA 3.1).  
It receives messages from Telegram users and replies instantly using AI.

---

## 🚀 Features

- 🤖 AI chatbot using LLaMA 3.1 (Groq API)
- 📩 Telegram bot integration
- ⚡ Fast real-time responses
- 🔐 Secure API key management using `.env`
- 🖥️ Console logging for debugging

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- Python 3.x
- python-telegram-bot
- OpenAI SDK (configured for Groq API)
- Groq API (LLaMA 3.1 model)
- python-dotenv

---

## 📁 Project Structure

project/  
├── bot.py              # Main bot script  
├── .env                # Environment variables (not shared)  
├── requirements.txt    # Dependencies (optional)  
└── README.md           # Project documentation  

---

## 🔑 Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file in the root folder:

TELEGRAM_TOKEN=your_telegram_bot_token  
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key  

---

## 📦 Installation

### 1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/telegram-ai-bot.git  
cd telegram-ai-bot  

---

### 2. Create virtual environment (optional)
python -m venv venv  

Activate it:

Windows:  
venv\Scripts\activate  

Mac/Linux:  
source venv/bin/activate  

---

### 3. Install dependencies
pip install python-telegram-bot openai python-dotenv  

---

## ▶️ Run the Bot

python bot.py  

If successful, you will see:

Bot Running...  

---

## 💬 How It Works

- User sends a message on Telegram  
- Bot receives message using MessageHandler  
- Message is sent to Groq API (LLaMA 3.1 model)  
- AI generates a response  
- Bot replies back in Telegram  

---

## ⚠️ Important Notes

- Do NOT upload `.env` file to GitHub  
- Keep your API keys secure  
- Internet connection is required for API calls  

---

